President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Missouri and authorized Federal assistance to aid in the recovery efforts of areas affected by severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from May 3 to May 4, 2020. The declaration allows for Federal funding to be provided to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The designated counties include Bates, Butler, Carter, Dallas, Douglas, Dunklin, Henry, Hickory, Howell, Laclede, New Madrid, Oregon, Pemiscot, Polk, Ripley, Shannon, Stoddard, Wayne, and Wright. Additionally, Federal funding is available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. John Brogan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.